                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d220">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.30 Asiatic Fleet/586: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Navy Department</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="42" xml:id="d220fn42">Copy of telegram from the commanding officer of
                        the U. S. S. <hi rend="italic">Oahu</hi> to the Commander of the United
                        States Yangtze Patrol.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-09-14T21:06:00+08:00"
                            >September 14, 1938—9:06 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 15—7 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>0014. Admiral Oikawa reaffirms his promise to ensure <hi rend="italic"
                        >Monocacy</hi> coal supply and is directing Nipponese SNO<note n="43"
                        xml:id="d220fn43">Senior Naval Officer.</note> Kiukiang to arrange delivery
                    25 tons weekly from Andersen, Meyer to Standard Vacuum installation. Request <hi
                        rend="italic">Monocacy</hi> check with Kondo<note n="44" xml:id="d220fn44"
                        >Rear Admiral Kondo, Imperial Japanese Navy.</note> and advise me before <hi
                        rend="italic">Oahu</hi> departs Shanghai.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
